CD to the sources folder and build the docker image

# docker build --rm -t <username>/ssh:centos7 .


To run:

# docker run -d -p 22 <username>/ssh:centos7

TIP: The username and password are settable in the start.sh script

Checkout the exposed port number

# docker ps


To test, use the port that was just located:

# ssh -p xxxx user@localhost 
